Preheat the oven to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1}, then halve lengthways. Chop each
half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 3cm pieces. Halve and
peel the @red onion{1}. Cut one half into 3 wedges, thinly slice the other half.
Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Halve the
@baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Pop the sweet potato, aubergine and onion wedges onto a large #baking tray{}.
> TIP: Use two trays if you need to. Drizzle with @olive oil{1.5%tbsp} then add the
@harissa paste{50%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat. Roast on
the top shelf of your oven until tender and golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Halfway
through cooking, turn the veg, then add the tomatoes and @chorizo{90%g} to the
tray to roast for the remaining ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, crumble the @feta cheese{100%g} into small pieces. Zest and cut the
@lemon{1/2} into wedges. Finely chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all), drain and
rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Heat a large #frying pan{} over medium heat
(no oil). Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15%g} and toast until lightly brown,
~{2-3%minutes}, stirring regularly (don't take your eye off them). Transfer the
almonds to a #bowl{} and set aside (we'll use the pan again in a second).

Squeeze the lemon juice into a bowl and add the @olive oil{75%ml}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the coriander and mix together. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in the frying pan on medium-high heat, add the sliced onion
and cook until soft, ~{5-6%minutes}, stir occasionally. Add the garlic and
@ground cumin{1} to the onion, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}. Pour in the
@water{75%ml} and stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil,
simmer until the water has reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the lentils
and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Once the veg has finished cooking, remove from the oven and add the vegetables to
the lentil pan. Add the lemon zest to the pan and mix everything together. Serve
into large #bowls{}, with the feta and toasted almonds sprinkled on top. Spoon
over the herby drizzle. Serve any remaining lemon wedges on the side. Enjoy!

> MOD Step: If you've opted to add chorizo to your meal, add it to the baking tray
> when you add the tomatoes and continue with the recipe as instructed.